b'Read the full statement from RBC CEO Dave McKay, including our commitment to take more meaningful action to support our communities:\n\xe2\x80\x9cGiven recent acts of racism and violence against the Black community, I feel it\xe2\x80\x99s important to share this message from our U.S. colleagues in Minneapolis. I\xe2\x80\x99m personally outraged at the senseless and tragic deaths in the U.S., which are clearly symptomatic of ongoing racial discrimination and injustice, and I know we are not immune to it in Canada. We must work harder to stop continued and systemic anti-Black racism, and the hate and discrimination that persists online in social media echo chambers. Diversity and inclusion is a core value at RBC and we are committed to making our workplaces, culture and communities both inclusive and welcoming for all. We need to continue on this journey every day, because in this divisive age, respect and empathy matters more than ever. Speaking up for inclusion and having uncomfortable conversations must happen year-round. But these are the moments when creating dialogue and having those conversations together \xe2\x80\x93 with greater empathy and understanding \xe2\x80\x93 is so important. It\xe2\x80\x99s also the time to take action. As a first step, our colleagues in Minneapolis will be donating $250,000 to help communities and businesses rebuild. And as an organization, we\xe2\x80\x99re committed to taking more meaningful action to support our communities and combat racism.\xe2\x80\x9d\n- Dave McKay, President & CEO, RBC'
